OL,3,CFive years to meet new limits on PFAS
OL,4,Cin water
OL,6,FHuman exposure to PFAS may occur
OL,7,Fthrough a number of ways, including
OL,8,Ffood and drinking water.
OL,10,FDespite how common it is, high levels
OL,11,Fof the chemicals have been linked to a
OL,12,Fnumber of health issue including some
OL,13,Fcancers, although the science and
OL,14,Fknowledge around risk factors are
OL,15,Fstill evolving.
