OL,3,CFive years to meet new limits on PFAS
OL,4,Cin water
OL,6,FJersey's Environment Minister Deputy
OL,7,FSteve Luce said: "The panel was clear
OL,8,Fthat it has recommended this lower
OL,9,Flimit in order to "future-proof" the
OL,10,FJersey drinking water supply, and that
OL,11,Fthere is no cause for concern over
OL,12,Fcurrent PFAS levels in the mains
OL,13,Fwater. The public water supply meets
OL,14,Fcurrent EU and UK standards for PFAS
OL,15,Flevels in drinking water.
